sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant FE as Frontend (PEAuth)
    participant API as Express API
    participant Auth as Supabase Auth
    participant DB as Supabase DB
    participant Org as orgMiddleware

    Note over U,DB: SIGNUP FLOW
    U->>FE: Fill signup form (name, email, password, firmName)
    FE->>Auth: supabase.auth.signUp(email, password)
    Auth-->>FE: Confirmation email sent
    U->>FE: Click verification link
    FE->>Auth: Email verified
    Auth-->>FE: Session + JWT token

    Note over U,DB: FIRST LOGIN — AUTO-PROVISION
    FE->>API: GET /api/users/me (JWT Bearer)
    API->>Auth: Verify JWT token
    Auth-->>API: authId (Supabase UUID)
    API->>Org: orgMiddleware — resolve user
    Org->>DB: SELECT User WHERE authId = ?
    DB-->>Org: NOT FOUND (PGRST116)
    Org->>DB: findOrCreateUser() — INSERT User + Organization
    DB-->>Org: New User (role=ADMIN) + New Org
    Org-->>API: req.organizationId set
    API-->>FE: User profile + org data

    Note over U,DB: SUBSEQUENT LOGIN
    U->>FE: Enter email + password
    FE->>Auth: supabase.auth.signInWithPassword()
    Auth-->>FE: JWT token + session
    FE->>FE: Store session (PEAuth singleton)
    FE->>API: PEAuth.authFetch() — all API calls
    API->>Auth: Verify JWT
    Auth-->>API: Valid — authId
    API->>Org: orgMiddleware
    Org->>DB: SELECT User WHERE authId = ?
    DB-->>Org: User found (organizationId, role)
    Org-->>API: req.organizationId + req.userId set
    API->>DB: Query with .eq('organizationId', orgId)
    DB-->>API: Org-scoped results only
    API-->>FE: Response data

    Note over U,DB: INVITATION FLOW
    U->>FE: Admin clicks Invite Team Member
    FE->>API: POST /api/invitations (email, role)
    API->>DB: INSERT Invitation (token, organizationId)
    API->>API: Send invite email via Resend
    API-->>FE: Invitation created

    Note over U,DB: ACCEPT INVITATION (PUBLIC)
    U->>FE: Click invite link — accept-invite.html?token=xxx
    FE->>API: GET /api/public/invitations/verify?token=xxx
    API->>DB: SELECT Invitation WHERE token = ?
    DB-->>API: Invitation (org name, logo, role)
    API-->>FE: Org info displayed
    U->>FE: Set password + accept
    FE->>Auth: supabase.auth.signUp(email, password)
    Auth-->>FE: User created in Supabase Auth
    FE->>API: POST /api/public/invitations/accept
    API->>DB: INSERT User (authId, organizationId, role)
    API->>DB: UPDATE Invitation SET status = ACCEPTED
    API-->>FE: Success — redirect to login

    Note over U,DB: PASSWORD RESET
    U->>FE: Click Forgot Password
    FE->>Auth: supabase.auth.resetPasswordForEmail()
    Auth-->>U: Reset email sent
    U->>FE: Click reset link
    FE->>Auth: supabase.auth.updateUser(newPassword)
    Auth-->>FE: Password updated
    FE->>FE: Redirect to login

    Note over U,DB: ROLE-BASED ACCESS
    FE->>API: Any protected request
    API->>Org: orgMiddleware resolves role

    alt ADMIN
        API->>API: Full access + admin features
    else MEMBER
        API->>API: Standard access, no admin
    else OPS
        API->>API: Operations access, limited AI
    else VIEWER
        API->>API: Read-only access
    end
    API-->>FE: Role-filtered response
